"title": "4254: mountains",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4254: mountains",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>These natural features of Palestine are often used as poetic symbols when describing God or his dealings with his people. Specific mountains are remembered because of their association with important events in the history of Israel. Some of the key events in the life and ministry of Jesus Christ take place on mountain sites.</p>\n<h2>Mountains and the character of God</h2>\n<h3>Mountains and the steadfastness of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:2\">PSA 125:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:1\">PSA 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:2\">PSA 90:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:10\">ISA 54:10</a></p>\n<h3>Mountains tremble at God's awesome presence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:5\">JDG 5:5</a></strong> <em>The violent physical response to the presence of the holy God evokes a sense of his might and majesty.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:16-Exod19:19\">EXO 19:16–19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:5\">PSA 97:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:1\">ISA 64:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic1:3-Mic1:4\">MIC 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:3-Hab3:6\">HAB 3:3–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>Mountains cannot stand before the anger of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:7\">PSA 18:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:23-Jer4:26\">JER 4:23–4:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:5-Nah1:6\">NAM 1:5–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:12-Rev6:14\">REV 6:12–6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:19-Rev16:20\">REV 16:19–16:20</a></p>\n<h2>Mountains as places of encounter with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1-Exod34:3\">EXO 34:1–34:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:11-1Kgs19:13\">1KI 19:11–19:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16-2Pet1:18\">2PE 1:16–1:18</a></p>\n<h2>Specific mountains as the sites of important events in Israel's history</h2>\n<h3>The mountains of Abarim: site of Israel's camp</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:47-Num33:48\">NUM 33:47–33:48</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Mount Ararat: resting place of Noah's ark</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:1-Gen8:5\">GEN 8:1–8:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Mount Carmel: scene of Elijah's defeat of the prophets of Baal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:16-1Kgs18:40\">1KI 18:16–18:40</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Mount Ebal: site of cursing; Mount Gerizim: site of blessing</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:29\">DEU 11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:30-Josh8:35\">JOS 8:30–8:35</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Gilboa: place of Saul's suicide</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:1-1Chr10:12\">1CH 10:1–10:12</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:1-1Sam31:13\">1SA 31:1–31:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:4-2Sam1:12\">2SA 1:4–1:12</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Hermon: a boundary of Israel</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:8\">DEU 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:16-Josh11:17\">JOS 11:16–11:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:6-Ps42:7\">PSA 42:6–42:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:12\">PSA 89:12</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Hor: place of Aaron's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:37-Num33:39\">NUM 33:37–33:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:22-Num20:29\">NUM 20:22–20:29</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Moriah: testing place of Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:1-Gen22:3\">GEN 22:1–22:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Mount Moriah: site of Solomon's temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:1\">2CH 3:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Mount Nebo: place of Moses' death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:48-Deut32:52\">DEU 32:48–32:52</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:1-Deut34:5\">DEU 34:1–34:5</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Sinai: God gives Moses the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:12\">EXO 24:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:18\">EXO 31:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:13-Neh9:14\">NEH 9:13–9:14</a></p>\n<h3>Mount Tabor: scene of Sisera's defeat</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:12-Judg4:16\">JDG 4:12–4:16</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Mountains as the sites of significant events in the NT</h2>\n<h3>On the Mount of Temptation the devil offers Jesus Christ the kingdoms of the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:8-Matt4:9\">MAT 4:8–4:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:5-Luke4:7\">LUK 4:5–4:7</a></p>\n<h3>In the Sermon on the Mount Jesus Christ teaches about life in the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:1-Matt5:2\">MAT 5:1–5:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>On the Mount of Transfiguration Jesus Christ's glory is revealed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1-Matt17:8\">MAT 17:1–17:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2-Mark9:8\">MRK 9:2–9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:28-Luke9:36\">LUK 9:28–9:36</a></p>\n<h3>On the Mount of Olives Jesus Christ teaches about the destruction of the temple and the last things</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:3\">MAT 24:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:3-Mark13:4\">MRK 13:3–13:4</a></p>",
